article.headline: Radford 111, VMI 84
article.story: LEXINGTON, Va. -- Art Parakhouski had 30 points and a school-record 22 rebounds to lead Radford to a 111-84 victory over Virginia Military Institute on Tuesday night. Parakhouski surpassed 1,000 career points in his 55th game and had the first 30-point, 20-rebound game in school history as the Highlanders (12-10, 8-4 Big South Conference) swept VMI this season. Lazar Trifunovic added 27 points and 12 rebounds and Joey Lynch-Flohr added 13 and 13 for Radford, which outrebounded VMI 62-36. The Highlanders led 55-44 at halftime and built a 67-50 margin on Amir Johnson's 3-pointer with 17:11 to play. Radford led 71-51 with 15:47 left. Radford shot 57.9 percent from the field (44-for-76) and 56.3 percent from the 3-point line (9-for-16). Johnson finished with 17 points. Michael Sparks scored 19, Austin Kenon had 18, Ron Burks added 17 and Stan Okoye had 12 for VMI (7-14, 2-9).
